Lapply is life lol. I think my most common code in R is: 

sapply(X = datatable, FUN = function(x){
mean(is.na(x)) 
})

faster version per my colleague Peter Wu rows_with_duplicate_cols_f <- function(dataset, column){ 
    # 50% faster when checked in profvis¬†
    dataset[ duplicated(dataset[[column]]) | 
             duplicated(dataset[[column]], fromLast = TRUE) , ] 
  }

Free function for this purpose:¬†

  rows_with_duplicate_cols <- function(dataset, column){ 
    dataset[ dataset[[column]] %in% 
             dataset[duplicated(dataset[[column]]), ][[column]],
           ]
  }

rows_with_duplicate_cols(mtcars, "mpg")¬†

